OL,3,CGovernment launches baby loss
OL,4,Ccertificate to 'recognise grief of
OL,5,Cparents'
OL,7,FBabies stillborn before 24 weeks do
OL,8,Fnot need to be officially registered,
OL,9,Fleaving some parents feeling ignored.
OL,11,FThe new certificates, which are not
OL,12,Fcompulsory, will be official but not
OL,13,Flegal documents.
OL,15,FThe idea was formed as part of the
OL,16,Fgovernment's response to the
OL,17,Findependent Pregnancy Loss Review,
OL,18,Fwith parents able to access the free
OL,19,Fservice on Thursday.
